article.headline: Drexel 55, Delaware 44
article.story: PHILADELPHIA (AP) -- Dominick Mejia hit back-to-back 3-pointers during a 13-1 run to lead Drexel to a 55-44 win over Delaware on Saturday afternoon. Mejia led the Dragons (11-8, 5-3 Colonial Athletic Association) to their second straight win with a game-high 17 points on 4-for-9 shooting from 3-point range. The first of Mejia's consecutive 3-pointers gave Drexel a 32-30 lead with 10:29 remaining. Drexel never trailed again. Delaware (5-12, 1-7) shot 33 percent from the field and was held to a season-low point total. Harding Nana scored a team-high 13 points for the Blue Hens, who have lost six of their last seven games. Herb Courtney added 11 points and 10 rebounds. Delaware trailed by as many as 13 in the first half, but used an 8-0 run midway through the second half to regain the lead. Drexel led 20-12 at halftime, after both teams struggled on offense. The Dragons shot 23 percent from the field (8-for-34) in the first half and the Blue Hens -- who made just one of their first 17 shots -- 21 percent (5-for-24). Chaz Crawford grabbed a game-high 12 rebounds for Drexel.
